'''脑回'''（Gyrus, 复数为gyri），为[[大脑皮质|大脑皮质]]中呈现隆起的部位，与呈现裂缝状的[[脑沟|脑沟]]相对<ref>{{Cite web|title=Gyri - an overview|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/neuroscience/gyri|access-date=2021-06-01|work=Science Direct|language=en | archive-date = 2017-08-24 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210602215726/https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/neuroscience/gyri | dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Toward a Common Terminology for the Gyri and Sulci of the Human Cerebral Cortex|url=https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnana.2018.00093/full|last=ten Donkelaar|first=Hans J.|last2=Tzourio-Mazoyer|first2=Nathalie|date=2018|journal=Frontiers in Neuroanatomy|doi=10.3389/fnana.2018.00093|volume=12|language=en|issn=1662-5129|last3=Mai|first3=Jürgen K. | archive-date = 2020-12-01 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210603025415/https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fnana.2018.00093/full | dead-url = no}}</ref>。出现脑回和脑沟的原因是，[[演化|演化]]过程中折叠结构使颅内相同容量下人类可以有更多[[大脑皮质|大脑皮质]]。较低等的动物则脑沟脑回较少<ref>{{Cite journal|title=The cerebral sulci and gyri|url=https://thejns.org/focus/view/journals/neurosurg-focus/28/2/article-pE2.xml|last=Ribas|first=Guilherme Carvalhal|date=2010-02-01|journal=Neurosurgical Focus|issue=2|doi=10.3171/2009.11.FOCUS09245|volume=28|pages=E2|language=en-US|issn=1092-0684 | archive-date = 2020-02-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210602235900/https://thejns.org/focus/view/journals/neurosurg-focus/28/2/article-pE2.xml | dead-url = no}}</ref>。

==結構==
腦回是脊狀褶曲系統的一部分，這讓人類大腦及其他哺乳動物的大腦創造了更大的表面積。<ref name="marieb">{{cite book | language = en | last1 = Marieb| first1 = Elaine N. | first2 = Katja| last2 = Hoehn | title =Human Anatomy & Physiology | publisher =Pearson | edition =9th | year =2012 | isbn = 978-0321852120 }}</ref>受限於頭骨的尺寸，使得大腦的體積是有限的。靠著隆起與凹陷產生的褶皺，讓皮質在受限於較小的[[顱骨|顱骨]]內可創造更大的表面積，同時增強了認知功能。<ref>{{cite journal| language = en |last1=Cusack|first1=Rhodri|title=The Intraparietal Sulcus and Perceptual Organization | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-cognitive-neuroscience_2005-04_17_4/page/641 |journal=Journal of Cognitive Neuroscience |date=2005-04-01 |volume=17 |issue=4 |pages=641–651 |doi=10.1162/0898929053467541 |pmid=15829084 |s2cid=25453338}}</ref>

===生長===
人腦在胎兒與新生兒發育過程中會經歷{{le|腦迴化|Gyrification}}階段。在[[胚胎|胚胎期]]過程中，所有[[哺乳動物|哺乳動物]]的大腦都是從{{le|神經管|Neural tube}}衍生的平滑結構分化而來。沒有表面褶皺的[[大脑皮质|大脑皮质]]被歸類為[[平腦症|平腦症]]，這是由於患有平腦症的大腦其表面相對較平滑。<ref>{{cite journal | language = en |last1=Armstrong |first1=E |last2=Schleicher |first2=A |last3=Omran |first3=H |last4=Curtis |first4=M |last5=Zilles |first5=K |title=The ontogeny of human gyrification. |journal=Cerebral Cortex |date=1991 |volume=5|issue=1|pages=56–63|pmid=7719130|doi=10.1093/cercor/5.1.56}}</ref> 隨著持續的發育，腦回和[[腦溝|腦溝]]在胎兒大腦逐漸形成，皮質表面也漸漸出現加深的凹陷及隆起結構。<ref>{{cite journal| language = en |last1=Rajagopalan|first1=V|last2=Scott|first2=J|last3=Habas|first3=PA|last4=Kim|first4=K|last5=Corbett-Detig |first5=J |last6=Rousseau |first6=F |last7=Barkovich |first7=AJ |last8=Glenn|first8=OA|last9=Studholme|first9=C |title=Local tissue growth patterns underlying normal fetal human brain gyrification quantified in utero.|journal=The Journal of Neuroscience |date=2011-02-23 |volume=31 |issue=8 |pages=2878–87 |pmid=21414909 |doi=10.1523/jneurosci.5458-10.2011 |pmc=3093305 | archive-date = 2021-03-08 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210308101859/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3093305/ | dead-url = no}}</ref>

==臨床意義==
大腦皮質的皺褶結構變化與各種疾病和障礙有關，如{{le|巨腦迴畸形|Pachygyria}}、[[平腦症|平腦症]]、{{le|多小腦迴畸形|polymicrogyria}}都是因異常[[細胞遷移|細胞遷移]]所導致的細胞結構紊亂等功能性問題，導致皮質神經元未能生成六層結構，僅生成四層結構的皮質神經元。<ref name="BarkovichGuerrini2012">{{cite journal| language = en |last1=Barkovich|first1=A. J.|last2=Guerrini|first2=R.|last3=Kuzniecky|first3=R. I.|last4=Jackson|first4=G. D.|last5=Dobyns|first5=W. B.|title=A developmental and genetic classification for malformations of cortical development: update 2012|journal=Brain|volume=135|issue=5|year=2012|pages=1348–1369|issn=0006-8950|doi=10.1093/brain/aws019|pmid=22427329|pmc=3338922 | archive-date = 2016-06-04 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160604173154/http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3338922/ | dead-url = no}}</ref>[[癲癇|癲癇]]及[[智能障礙|智能障礙]]等疾病通常與這類大腦皮質異常形成有關連。<ref name="PangAtefy2008">{{cite journal| language = en |last1=Pang |first1=Trudy |last2=Atefy |first2=Ramin |last3=Sheen |first3=Volney |title=Malformations of Cortical Development|journal=The Neurologist |volume=14 |issue=3 |year=2008 |pages=181–191 |issn=1074-7931 |doi=10.1097/NRL.0b013e31816606b9 |pmid=18469675 |pmc=3547618 | archive-date = 2021-07-18 | archive-url = https://archive.vn/EKjd6 | dead-url = no}}</ref>

巨腦迴畸形（意指較厚或較肥的腦回）是[[大腦半球|大腦半球]]的先天性畸形，導致大腦皮質的腦迴異常肥厚。巨腦迴畸形常用於描述與幾種{{le|神經元移行障礙|Neuronal migration disorder}}相關的大腦異常特徵，其中最常與平腦畸形有關。<ref name=guerrini5>{{cite journal | language = en |author=Guerrini R |title=Genetic malformations of the cerebral cortex and epilepsy |journal=Epilepsia |volume=46 Suppl 1 |pages=32–37 |year=2005 |pmid=15816977 |doi=10.1111/j.0013-9580.2005.461010.x |s2cid=24119081 |doi-access=free }}</ref>

平腦症是一種罕見的先天性腦畸形疾病，主要是在胎兒妊娠第12至第24週期間時發生神經元移行障礙，使得腦回和腦溝發展出現缺陷所致。<ref>{{cite journal | language = en |author=Dobyns WB |title=Developmental aspects of lissencephaly and the lissencephaly syndromes |journal=Birth Defects Orig. Artic. Ser. |volume=23 |issue=1 |pages=225–41 |year=1987 |pmid=3472611 }}</ref>多小腦迴畸形也是人類大腦發育畸形的疾病之一，其特徵是腦回過度折疊及大腦皮質增厚等。<ref name="chang">{{cite journal | language = en |last1=Chang |first1=B |last2=Walsh |first2=CA |last3=Apse |first3=K |title=Polymicrogyria Overview |journal=GeneReviews |pmid=20301504 |year=1993 |last4=Bodell |first4=A |last5=Pagon |first5=RA |last6=Adam |first6=TD |last7=Bird |first7=CR |last8=Dolan |first8=K |last9=Fong |first9=MP |last10=Stephens |first10=K}}</ref>該病症可能是全面性的，如影響大腦皮質整個表面，也可能是局灶性的，如僅影響皮質表面的一部分。多小腦迴畸形可能由幾個[[基因|基因]]突變所引起的，而這也包括影響[[離子通道|離子通道]]運作等。<ref>{{cite journal | language = en |last1=Smith |first1=RS |last2=Walsh |first2=CA |title=Ion Channel Functions in Early Brain Development. |journal=Trends in Neurosciences |date=2020-01-17 |volume=43 |issue=2 |pages=103–114 |doi=10.1016/j.tins.2019.12.004 |pmid=31959360 |pmc=7092371 | archive-date = 2021-07-18 | archive-url = https://archive.ph/HpjU6 | dead-url = no}}</ref>

